ion entity: :task/t-9f0aedd9; Session entity: :recon/trace-6bf03a28b0ce4026; Session entity: :task/t-f027f9fb; Session entity: :task/t-43b96f49; Session entity: :recon/trace-c100fa1196a4082b; Session entity: :recon/trace-8ce36400a7484c42; Session entity: :recon/trace-53b61b083d90665e; Session entity: :task/t-5bfc6cd5; Session entity: :recon/trace-c8a2f21a133aaac8; Session entity: :recon/trace-1e8028f50e013ab5; Session entity: :recon/trace-a7bc21dc6d8ea033; Session entity: :task/t-e532c65c; Session entity: :task/t-03f867f7; Prolly Tree Staged Migration; Session entity: :config/concept-join-threshold; Session entity: :recon/trace-136b87762fea87ac; Session entity: :recon/trace-81dd8065946015b9; Session entity: :recon/trace-419c4413b1d7d3d8; Session entity: :task/t-11cd0f7d; Policy-Driven Fitness Function; Session entity: :task/t-85996e37; Session entity: :recon/trace-1ba49df99bd370ff; Session entity: :task/t-2bd59586; Session entity: :recon/trace-322be131970b80ac; Session entity: :recon/trace-554bada7191853eb; Session entity: :task/t-82dc0ee6; Session entity: :recon/trace-9dbea2e21a7dc860; Session entity: :task/t-290a46c3; Session entity: :recon/trace-fbc5ed9ab75c24fb; Session entity: :recon/trace-75e4d29915502833; Session entity: :task/t-315f6b6d; Session entity: :config/concept-sigmoid-temperature; Session entity: :recon/trace-93f2f65f317d8084; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-count; Session entity: :recon/trace-2b725c93e63b52bf; Session entity: :recon/trace-1c3ba1c4a64703b3; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-sum; Session entity: :recon/trace-dbcf35b3ea62d0f4; Session entity: :task/t-a395d458\nSession entity: :task/t-1a20a2e9; Session entity: :task/t-b569197c; Session entity: :task/t-c910d6b2; Session entity: :task/t-08b2089b; CRITICAL BUG FIX: Stale cache overwrite race condition. When main.rs LiveStore (dirty from session detection) drops AFTER a command's own LiveStore, it overwrites store.bin with stale state. Command writes become invisible through cache. Root cause: L1-SINGLE created overlapping LiveStore lifetimes. Fix: (1) session detection only for commands using pre_opened store, (2) defensive flush guard in LiveStore::flush() — skip if has_new_external_txns(). Verified: task create + immediate search now works.; Single-Writer Cache Safety; Session entity: :task/t-075af7ae; PROPOSAL: Slim Cache Format (INV-CACHE-001). The store.bin serializes P union D where P=primary(datoms,frontier,schema,clock,views) and D=derived(5 indexes). D=phi(P) where phi=from_datoms is a deterministic free functor. Current: serialize P+D=110MB, deserialize ~2000ms. Proposed: serialize only P with zstd compression ~18MB, rebuild D on load via from_primary() ~120ms. Net: I/O drops from 2000ms to 350ms. Verification: proptest round-trip (serialize_primary -> deserialize -> rebuild_indexes == original). Dependencies: needs Store::from_primary() in kernel, SlimCache struct in layout.rs, zstd crate. Traces: SEED.md S4 (store is P(D) union), INV-STORE-020, ADR-STORE-005.; ANALYSIS: Store.bin composition at 140K datoms. Primary state: datoms BTreeSet ~74MB (60%), frontier+schema+clock <1MB, MaterializedViews ~8MB (5%). Derived indexes: entity_index ~18.5MB, attribute_index ~12.5MB, vaet_index ~2.5MB, avet_index ~10MB, live_view ~2.5MB. Total derived: ~46MB (37%). With zstd level 3: primary ~74MB compresses to ~15-20MB (structured strings compress well). Decompression at ~1GB/s: 15-20ms. Total estimated load path: read 18MB (50ms) + decompress (15ms) + bincode deserialize (300ms) + index rebuild (120ms) = ~485ms. Traces: INV-PERF-001, INV-CACHE-005.; Session entity: :task/t-abccebc1; PROPOSAL: Single-Writer Linearity (INV-CACHE-002). store.bin is a linear resource -- exactly one writer at a time. Current: multiple LiveStore instances compete for store.bin, last Drop wins. Bug: stale overwrite makes writes invisible. Root cause: main.rs holds dirty LiveStore while command opens its own. Fix: wire pre_opened to ALL write commands so one LiveStore handles all writes. Defensive: flush() checks has_new_external_txns() before overwriting. Session detection restricted to pre_opened commands only. Verification: create task -> immediate search must succeed. Dependencies: change signatures of observe, task, harvest, query, seed, spec, write commands. Traces: INV-STORE-022, ADR-FOUNDATION-034, C1.; Single-Writer Cache Linearity; Cache Load Latency Bound; FINDING: F(S) structural ceiling at 0.62. Anti-correlation between I(incompleteness) and C/V(coverage/validation): new specs enter I at floor 0.15, diluting mean. K+U contribute 0.249 and are always near max, masking real gaps. Hypothesis ledger error degraded 0.224->0.521 confirming routing predictions diverge from F(S) reality by 84%. MaterializedViews vs batch F(S) divergence unresolved (SOUND-ISO). Proposed fix: replace 7-component weighted sum with policy-driven F(S) from BoundaryRegistry. Each boundary contributes alignment score, weights from policy manifest. Eliminates structural ceiling AND fixes C8 simultaneously. Traces: ADR-FOUNDATION-014, INV-BILATERAL-001, ADR-STORE-006.; Primary Sufficiency; ARCHITECTURE: Four-phase dependency chain. Phase 1 (Perf) -> Phase 2 (F(S)) -> Phase 3 (C8) -> Phase 4 (Validation). Formal justification: Phase 1 unblocks iteration (3.7s -> 0.8s saves 145s/session over 5 sessions). Phase 2 dissolves F(S) ceiling (prerequisite for meaningful convergence measurement). Phase 3 enables external validation (C8 fixes meaningless without correct metric). Phase 4 proves substrate independence empirically. Skip any phase and chain breaks: skip 1 = 4.6x slower iteration; skip 2 = F(S) remains capped regardless of C8 fixes; skip 3 = external validation fails on hardcoded patterns; skip 4 = no empirical test of bedrock claim. Traces: ADR-FOUNDATION-014, C8, INV-PERF-001.; PROPOSAL: External Validation (S0-CLOSE). 47 sessions of DDIS-on-DDIS without external validation. DOGFOOD-2 score 3.48/10. Substrate independence claim is architecturally clean but empirically untested. Proposed: run braid on React/Go project with custom policy manifest, execute 3 harvest/seed cycles, measure seed quality and guidance utility. Combined with verification sprint on braid itself (zero new specs, only test existing INVs). Falsification: external seed quality < 5/10 means C8 violations remain. F(S) doesn't move after verification sprint means structural ceiling persists. Traces: C8, ADR-FOUNDATION-014, INV-FOUNDATION-006.; PROPOSAL: Prolly Tree Migration Path (Stage 2-3). BTreeMap is correct for current stage (in-memory, single-process). Prolly trees become compelling at Stage 2 (branching: O(1) cheap snapshots) and Stage 3 (multi-agent: O(d) merge instead of O(n)). History independence aligns with C2 (identity by content). Root hash = cryptographic commitment to entire store. Recommended crate: merkle-search-tree (domodwyer, used at InfluxDB) -- designed as state-based CRDT for key-value maps, exactly braid's semilattice. Migration clean: prolly trees implement same sorted-map interface. Slim cache proposal designed so persistence layer swap doesn't touch query layer. Traces: C2, C4, SEED.md S4, ADR-STORE-005.; FINDING: 7 C8 violations in kernel. (1) spec_id.rs:53 enforces INV/ADR/NEG only. (2-4) methodology.rs:389,444 and seed.rs:908,2820,3014 hardcode :spec/ prefix. (5) methodology.rs:908 hardcodes :spec/falsification. (6) task.rs:70-111 hardcodes 7 task types. (7) config.rs:149 defaults to crates/ for trace source. DOGFOOD-2: 3.48/10 on external Go project. Seed loses 28% sections on non-DDIS projects. Fix: parameterize SpecId from policy, replace :spec/ with policy queries, make task types schema-driven. Must follow F(S) redesign (Phase 2 before Phase 3). Traces: C8, INV-FOUNDATION-006, ADR-FOUNDATION-012.; Index Rebuild Isomorphism; Compression Round-Trip Integrity" :op :assert}
